      "Metal band excess slack cut off to reduce sharp edges"
    ],
    "summary": "On June 7, 2021, at approximately 1415 hours on MC 474 A (Na Kika), a BP employee suffered a laceration to the right ring finger while loosening a TMC Connector on a transmitter with channel lock pliers. The laceration was caused by a sharp edge on a metal band used to secure identification tags, located 3-4 inches from the TMC Connector. The worker was wearing gloves at the time but they did not provide adequate protection. The injury required four sutures and a tetanus shot.",
    "recommendations": [
      "Metal band should be installed to eliminate sharp edges",
      "Gloves worn should provide adequate protection for the task"
    ],
